131/*!



132 * @file S32K144.h



133 * @version 4.0



134 * @date 2018-02-28



135 * @brief Peripheral Access Layer for S32K144



136 *



137 * This file contains register definitions and macros for easy access to their



138 * bit fields.



139 *



140 * This file assumes LITTLE endian system.



141 */



142



143/**



144* @page misra_violations MISRA-C:2012 violations



145*



146* @section [global]



147* Violates MISRA 2012 Advisory Rule 2.3, local typedef not referenced



148* The SoC header defines typedef for all modules.



149*



150* @section [global]



151* Violates MISRA 2012 Advisory Rule 2.5, local macro not referenced



152* The SoC header defines macros for all modules and registers.



153*



154* @section [global]



155* Violates MISRA 2012 Advisory Directive 4.9, Function-like macro



156* These are generated macros used for accessing the bit-fields from registers.



157*



158* @section [global]



159* Violates MISRA 2012 Required Rule 5.1, identifier clash



160* The supported compilers use more than 31 significant characters for identifiers.



161*



162* @section [global]



163* Violates MISRA 2012 Required Rule 5.2, identifier clash



164* The supported compilers use more than 31 significant characters for identifiers.



165*



166* @section [global]



167* Violates MISRA 2012 Required Rule 5.4, identifier clash



168* The supported compilers use more than 31 significant characters for identifiers.



169*



170* @section [global]



171* Violates MISRA 2012 Required Rule 5.5, identifier clash



172* The supported compilers use more than 31 significant characters for identifiers.



173*



174* @section [global]



175* Violates MISRA 2012 Required Rule 21.1, defined macro '__I' is reserved to the compiler



176* This type qualifier is needed to ensure correct I/O access and addressing.



177*/



178

183/* Prevention from multiple including the same memory map */



184#if !defined(S32K144_H_)  /* Check if memory map has not been already included */



185#define S32K144_H_



186#define MCU_S32K144



187



188/* Check if another memory map has not been also included */



189#if (defined(MCU_ACTIVE))



190  #error S32K144 memory map: There is already included another memory map. Only one memory map can be included.



191#endif /* (defined(MCU_ACTIVE)) */



192#define MCU_ACTIVE



193



194#include <stdint.h>



195



196/** Memory map major version (memory maps with equal major version number are



197 * compatible) */



198#define MCU_MEM_MAP_VERSION 0x0400u



199/** Memory map minor version */



200#define MCU_MEM_MAP_VERSION_MINOR 0x0000u



201



202/* ----------------------------------------------------------------------------



203   -- Generic macros



204   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- */



205



206/* IO definitions (access restrictions to peripheral registers) */



207/**



208*   IO Type Qualifiers are used



209*   \li to specify the access to peripheral variables.



210*   \li for automatic generation of peripheral register debug information.



211*/



212#ifndef __IO



213#ifdef __cplusplus



214  #define   __I     volatile             /*!< Defines 'read only' permissions                 */



215#else



216  #define   __I     volatile const       /*!< Defines 'read only' permissions                 */



217#endif



218#define     __O     volatile             /*!< Defines 'write only' permissions                */



219#define     __IO    volatile             /*!< Defines 'read / write' permissions              */



220#endif



221



222



223/**



224* @brief 32 bits memory read macro.



225*/



226#if !defined(REG_READ32)



227  #define REG_READ32(address)               (*(volatile uint32_t*)(address))



228#endif



229



230/**



231* @brief 32 bits memory write macro.



232*/



233#if !defined(REG_WRITE32)



234  #define REG_WRITE32(address, value)       ((*(volatile uint32_t*)(address))= (uint32_t)(value))



235#endif



236



237/**



238* @brief 32 bits bits setting macro.



239*/



240#if !defined(REG_BIT_SET32)



241  #define REG_BIT_SET32(address, mask)      ((*(volatile uint32_t*)(address))|= (uint32_t)(mask))



242#endif



243



244/**



245* @brief 32 bits bits clearing macro.



246*/



247#if !defined(REG_BIT_CLEAR32)



248  #define REG_BIT_CLEAR32(address, mask)    ((*(volatile uint32_t*)(address))&= ((uint32_t)~((uint32_t)(mask))))



249#endif



250



251/**



252* @brief 32 bit clear bits and set with new value



253* @note It is user's responsability to make sure that value has only "mask" bits set - (value&~mask)==0



254*/



255#if !defined(REG_RMW32)



256  #define REG_RMW32(address, mask, value)   (REG_WRITE32((address), ((REG_READ32(address)& ((uint32_t)~((uint32_t)(mask))))| ((uint32_t)(value)))))



257#endif



258



259

269/** Interrupt Number Definitions */



270#define NUMBER_OF_INT_VECTORS 139u               /**< Number of interrupts in the Vector table */



271



272/**



273 * @brief Defines the Interrupt Numbers definitions



274 *



275 * This enumeration is used to configure the interrupts.



276 *



277 * Implements : IRQn_Type_Class



278 */



279typedef enum



280{



281  /* Auxiliary constants */



282  NotAvail_IRQn                = -128,             /**< Not available device specific interrupt */



283



284  /* Core interrupts */



285  NonMaskableInt_IRQn          = -14,              /**< Non Maskable Interrupt */



286  HardFault_IRQn               = -13,              /**< Cortex-M4 SV Hard Fault Interrupt */



287  MemoryManagement_IRQn        = -12,              /**< Cortex-M4 Memory Management Interrupt */



288  BusFault_IRQn                = -11,              /**< Cortex-M4 Bus Fault Interrupt */



289  UsageFault_IRQn              = -10,              /**< Cortex-M4 Usage Fault Interrupt */



290  SVCall_IRQn                  = -5,               /**< Cortex-M4 SV Call Interrupt */



291  DebugMonitor_IRQn            = -4,               /**< Cortex-M4 Debug Monitor Interrupt */



292  PendSV_IRQn                  = -2,               /**< Cortex-M4 Pend SV Interrupt */



293  SysTick_IRQn                 = -1,               /**< Cortex-M4 System Tick Interrupt */



294



295  /* Device specific interrupts */



296  DMA0_IRQn                    = 0u,               /**< DMA channel 0 transfer complete */



297  DMA1_IRQn                    = 1u,               /**< DMA channel 1 transfer complete */



298  DMA2_IRQn                    = 2u,               /**< DMA channel 2 transfer complete */



299  DMA3_IRQn                    = 3u,               /**< DMA channel 3 transfer complete */



300  DMA4_IRQn                    = 4u,               /**< DMA channel 4 transfer complete */



301  DMA5_IRQn                    = 5u,               /**< DMA channel 5 transfer complete */



302  DMA6_IRQn                    = 6u,               /**< DMA channel 6 transfer complete */



303  DMA7_IRQn                    = 7u,               /**< DMA channel 7 transfer complete */



304  DMA8_IRQn                    = 8u,               /**< DMA channel 8 transfer complete */



305  DMA9_IRQn                    = 9u,               /**< DMA channel 9 transfer complete */



306  DMA10_IRQn                   = 10u,              /**< DMA channel 10 transfer complete */



307  DMA11_IRQn                   = 11u,              /**< DMA channel 11 transfer complete */



308  DMA12_IRQn                   = 12u,              /**< DMA channel 12 transfer complete */



309  DMA13_IRQn                   = 13u,              /**< DMA channel 13 transfer complete */



310  DMA14_IRQn                   = 14u,              /**< DMA channel 14 transfer complete */



311  DMA15_IRQn                   = 15u,              /**< DMA channel 15 transfer complete */



312  DMA_Error_IRQn               = 16u,              /**< DMA error interrupt channels 0-15 */



313  MCM_IRQn                     = 17u,              /**< FPU sources */



314  FTFC_IRQn                    = 18u,              /**< FTFC Command complete */



315  Read_Collision_IRQn          = 19u,              /**< FTFC Read collision */



316  LVD_LVW_IRQn                 = 20u,              /**< PMC Low voltage detect interrupt */



317  FTFC_Fault_IRQn              = 21u,              /**< FTFC Double bit fault detect */



318  WDOG_EWM_IRQn                = 22u,              /**< Single interrupt vector for WDOG and EWM */



319  RCM_IRQn                     = 23u,              /**< RCM Asynchronous Interrupt */



320  LPI2C0_Master_IRQn           = 24u,              /**< LPI2C0 Master Interrupt */



321  LPI2C0_Slave_IRQn            = 25u,              /**< LPI2C0 Slave Interrupt */



322  LPSPI0_IRQn                  = 26u,              /**< LPSPI0 Interrupt */



323  LPSPI1_IRQn                  = 27u,              /**< LPSPI1 Interrupt */



324  LPSPI2_IRQn                  = 28u,              /**< LPSPI2 Interrupt */



325  LPUART0_RxTx_IRQn            = 31u,              /**< LPUART0 Transmit / Receive Interrupt */



326  LPUART1_RxTx_IRQn            = 33u,              /**< LPUART1 Transmit / Receive  Interrupt */



327  LPUART2_RxTx_IRQn            = 35u,              /**< LPUART2 Transmit / Receive  Interrupt */



328  ADC0_IRQn                    = 39u,              /**< ADC0 interrupt request. */



329  ADC1_IRQn                    = 40u,              /**< ADC1 interrupt request. */



330  CMP0_IRQn                    = 41u,              /**< CMP0 interrupt request */



331  ERM_single_fault_IRQn        = 44u,              /**< ERM single bit error correction */



332  ERM_double_fault_IRQn        = 45u,              /**< ERM double bit error non-correctable */



333  RTC_IRQn                     = 46u,              /**< RTC alarm interrupt */



334  RTC_Seconds_IRQn             = 47u,              /**< RTC seconds interrupt */



335  LPIT0_Ch0_IRQn               = 48u,              /**< LPIT0 channel 0 overflow interrupt */



336  LPIT0_Ch1_IRQn               = 49u,              /**< LPIT0 channel 1 overflow interrupt */



337  LPIT0_Ch2_IRQn               = 50u,              /**< LPIT0 channel 2 overflow interrupt */



338  LPIT0_Ch3_IRQn               = 51u,              /**< LPIT0 channel 3 overflow interrupt */



339  PDB0_IRQn                    = 52u,              /**< PDB0 interrupt */



340  SCG_IRQn                     = 57u,              /**< SCG bus interrupt request */



341  LPTMR0_IRQn                  = 58u,              /**< LPTIMER interrupt request */



342  PORTA_IRQn                   = 59u,              /**< Port A pin detect interrupt */



343  PORTB_IRQn                   = 60u,              /**< Port B pin detect interrupt */



344  PORTC_IRQn                   = 61u,              /**< Port C pin detect interrupt */



345  PORTD_IRQn                   = 62u,              /**< Port D pin detect interrupt */



346  PORTE_IRQn                   = 63u,              /**< Port E pin detect interrupt */



347  SWI_IRQn                     = 64u,              /**< Software interrupt */



348  PDB1_IRQn                    = 68u,              /**< PDB1 interrupt */



349  FLEXIO_IRQn                  = 69u,              /**< FlexIO Interrupt */



350  CAN0_ORed_IRQn               = 78u,              /**< CAN0 OR'ed [Bus Off OR Transmit Warning OR Receive Warning] */



351  CAN0_Error_IRQn              = 79u,              /**< CAN0 Interrupt indicating that errors were detected on the CAN bus */



352  CAN0_Wake_Up_IRQn            = 80u,              /**< CAN0 Interrupt asserted when Pretended Networking operation is enabled, and a valid message matches the selected filter criteria during Low Power mode */



353  CAN0_ORed_0_15_MB_IRQn       = 81u,              /**< CAN0 OR'ed Message buffer (0-15) */



354  CAN0_ORed_16_31_MB_IRQn      = 82u,              /**< CAN0 OR'ed Message buffer (16-31) */

356  CAN1_Error_IRQn              = 86u,              /**< CAN1 Interrupt indicating that errors were detected on the CAN bus */



357  CAN1_ORed_0_15_MB_IRQn       = 88u,              /**< CAN1 OR'ed Interrupt for Message buffer (0-15) */



358  CAN2_ORed_IRQn               = 92u,              /**< CAN2 OR'ed [Bus Off OR Transmit Warning OR Receive Warning] */



359  CAN2_Error_IRQn              = 93u,              /**< CAN2 Interrupt indicating that errors were detected on the CAN bus */



360  CAN2_ORed_0_15_MB_IRQn       = 95u,              /**< CAN2 OR'ed Message buffer (0-15) */



361  FTM0_Ch0_Ch1_IRQn            = 99u,              /**< FTM0 Channel 0 and 1 interrupt */



362  FTM0_Ch2_Ch3_IRQn            = 100u,             /**< FTM0 Channel 2 and 3 interrupt */



363  FTM0_Ch4_Ch5_IRQn            = 101u,             /**< FTM0 Channel 4 and 5 interrupt */



364  FTM0_Ch6_Ch7_IRQn            = 102u,             /**< FTM0 Channel 6 and 7 interrupt */



365  FTM0_Fault_IRQn              = 103u,             /**< FTM0 Fault interrupt */



366  FTM0_Ovf_Reload_IRQn         = 104u,             /**< FTM0 Counter overflow and Reload interrupt */



367  FTM1_Ch0_Ch1_IRQn            = 105u,             /**< FTM1 Channel 0 and 1 interrupt */



368  FTM1_Ch2_Ch3_IRQn            = 106u,             /**< FTM1 Channel 2 and 3 interrupt */



369  FTM1_Ch4_Ch5_IRQn            = 107u,             /**< FTM1 Channel 4 and 5 interrupt */



370  FTM1_Ch6_Ch7_IRQn            = 108u,             /**< FTM1 Channel 6 and 7 interrupt */



371  FTM1_Fault_IRQn              = 109u,             /**< FTM1 Fault interrupt */



372  FTM1_Ovf_Reload_IRQn         = 110u,             /**< FTM1 Counter overflow and Reload interrupt */



373  FTM2_Ch0_Ch1_IRQn            = 111u,             /**< FTM2 Channel 0 and 1 interrupt */



374  FTM2_Ch2_Ch3_IRQn            = 112u,             /**< FTM2 Channel 2 and 3 interrupt */



375  FTM2_Ch4_Ch5_IRQn            = 113u,             /**< FTM2 Channel 4 and 5 interrupt */



376  FTM2_Ch6_Ch7_IRQn            = 114u,             /**< FTM2 Channel 6 and 7 interrupt */



377  FTM2_Fault_IRQn              = 115u,             /**< FTM2 Fault interrupt */



378  FTM2_Ovf_Reload_IRQn         = 116u,             /**< FTM2 Counter overflow and Reload interrupt */



379  FTM3_Ch0_Ch1_IRQn            = 117u,             /**< FTM3 Channel 0 and 1 interrupt */

403/* ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

407/*!



408 * @addtogroup ADC_Peripheral_Access_Layer ADC Peripheral Access Layer



409 * @{



410 */



411



412



413/** ADC - Size of Registers Arrays */



414#define ADC_SC1_COUNT                            16u



415#define ADC_R_COUNT                              16u



416#define ADC_CV_COUNT                             2u



417



418/** ADC - Register Layout Typedef */



419typedef struct {



420  __IO uint32_t SC1[ADC_SC1_COUNT];                /**< ADC Status and Control Register 1, array offset: 0x0, array step: 0x4 */



421  __IO uint32_t CFG1;                              /**< ADC Configuration Register 1, offset: 0x40 */



422  __IO uint32_t CFG2;                              /**< ADC Configuration Register 2, offset: 0x44 */



423  __I  uint32_t R[ADC_R_COUNT];                    /**< ADC Data Result Registers, array offset: 0x48, array step: 0x4 */



424  __IO uint32_t CV[ADC_CV_COUNT];                  /**< Compare Value Registers, array offset: 0x88, array step: 0x4 */



425  __IO uint32_t SC2;                               /**< Status and Control Register 2, offset: 0x90 */



426  __IO uint32_t SC3;                               /**< Status and Control Register 3, offset: 0x94 */



427  __IO uint32_t BASE_OFS;                          /**< BASE Offset Register, offset: 0x98 */



428  __IO uint32_t OFS;                               /**< ADC Offset Correction Register, offset: 0x9C */



429  __IO uint32_t USR_OFS;                           /**< USER Offset Correction Register, offset: 0xA0 */



430  __IO uint32_t XOFS;                              /**< ADC X Offset Correction Register, offset: 0xA4 */



431  __IO uint32_t YOFS;                              /**< ADC Y Offset Correction Register, offset: 0xA8 */



432  __IO uint32_t G;                                 /**< ADC Gain Register, offset: 0xAC */



433  __IO uint32_t UG;                                /**< ADC User Gain Register, offset: 0xB0 */



434  __IO uint32_t CLPS;                              /**< ADC General Calibration Value Register S, offset: 0xB4 */



435  __IO uint32_t CLP3;                              /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register 3, offset: 0xB8 */



436  __IO uint32_t CLP2;                              /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register 2, offset: 0xBC */



437  __IO uint32_t CLP1;                              /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register 1, offset: 0xC0 */



438  __IO uint32_t CLP0;                              /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register 0, offset: 0xC4 */



439  __IO uint32_t CLPX;                              /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register X, offset: 0xC8 */



440  __IO uint32_t CLP9;                              /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Value Register 9, offset: 0xCC */



441  __IO uint32_t CLPS_OFS;                          /**< ADC General Calibration Offset Value Register S, offset: 0xD0 */



442  __IO uint32_t CLP3_OFS;                          /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Offset Value Register 3, offset: 0xD4 */



443  __IO uint32_t CLP2_OFS;                          /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Offset Value Register 2, offset: 0xD8 */



444  __IO uint32_t CLP1_OFS;                          /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Offset Value Register 1, offset: 0xDC */



445  __IO uint32_t CLP0_OFS;                          /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Offset Value Register 0, offset: 0xE0 */



446  __IO uint32_t CLPX_OFS;                          /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Offset Value Register X, offset: 0xE4 */



447  __IO uint32_t CLP9_OFS;                          /**< ADC Plus-Side General Calibration Offset Value Register 9, offset: 0xE8 */



448} ADC_Type, *ADC_MemMapPtr;



449



450 /** Number of instances of the ADC module. */



451#define ADC_INSTANCE_COUNT                       (2u)



452



453



454/* ADC - Peripheral instance base addresses */



455/** Peripheral ADC0 base address */



456#define ADC0_BASE                                (0x4003B000u)



457/** Peripheral ADC0 base pointer */



458#define ADC0                                     ((ADC_Type *)ADC0_BASE)



459/** Peripheral ADC1 base address */



460#define ADC1_BASE                                (0x40027000u)



461/** Peripheral ADC1 base pointer */



462#define ADC1                                     ((ADC_Type *)ADC1_BASE)



463/** Array initializer of ADC peripheral base addresses */



464#define ADC_BASE_ADDRS                           { ADC0_BASE, ADC1_BASE }



465/** Array initializer of ADC peripheral base pointers */



466#define ADC_BASE_PTRS                            { ADC0, ADC1 }



467 /** Number of interrupt vector arrays for the ADC module. */



468#define ADC_IRQS_ARR_COUNT                       (1u)



469 /** Number of interrupt channels for the ADC module. */



470#define ADC_IRQS_CH_COUNT                        (1u)

711



712/** AIPS - Size of Registers Arrays */



713#define AIPS_PACR_COUNT                          4u



714#define AIPS_OPACR_COUNT                         12u



715



716/** AIPS - Register Layout Typedef */



717typedef struct {



718  __IO uint32_t MPRA;                              /**< Master Privilege Register A, offset: 0x0 */



719       uint8_t RESERVED_0[28];



720  __IO uint32_t PACR[AIPS_PACR_COUNT];             /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, array offset: 0x20, array step: 0x4 */



721       uint8_t RESERVED_1[16];



722  __IO uint32_t OPACR[AIPS_OPACR_COUNT];           /**< Off-Platform Peripheral Access Control Register, array offset: 0x40, array step: 0x4 */



723} AIPS_Type, *AIPS_MemMapPtr;



724



725 /** Number of instances of the AIPS module. */



726#define AIPS_INSTANCE_COUNT                      (1u)



727



728



729/* AIPS - Peripheral instance base addresses */



730/** Peripheral AIPS base address */



731#define AIPS_BASE                                (0x40000000u)



732/** Peripheral AIPS base pointer */



733#define AIPS                                     ((AIPS_Type *)AIPS_BASE)



734/** Array initializer of AIPS peripheral base addresses */



735#define AIPS_BASE_ADDRS                          { AIPS_BASE }



736/** Array initializer of AIPS peripheral base pointers */



737#define AIPS_BASE_PTRS                           { AIPS }

939



940/** CAN - Size of Registers Arrays */



941#define CAN_RAMn_COUNT                           128u



942#define CAN_RXIMR_COUNT                          32u



943#define CAN_WMB_COUNT                            4u



944



945/** CAN - Register Layout Typedef */



946typedef struct {



947  __IO uint32_t MCR;                               /**< Module Configuration Register, offset: 0x0 */



948  __IO uint32_t CTRL1;                             /**< Control 1 register, offset: 0x4 */



949  __IO uint32_t TIMER;                             /**< Free Running Timer, offset: 0x8 */



950       uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];



951  __IO uint32_t RXMGMASK;                          /**< Rx Mailboxes Global Mask Register, offset: 0x10 */



952  __IO uint32_t RX14MASK;                          /**< Rx 14 Mask register, offset: 0x14 */



953  __IO uint32_t RX15MASK;                          /**< Rx 15 Mask register, offset: 0x18 */



954  __IO uint32_t ECR;                               /**< Error Counter, offset: 0x1C */



955  __IO uint32_t ESR1;                              /**< Error and Status 1 register, offset: 0x20 */



956       uint8_t RESERVED_1[4];



957  __IO uint32_t IMASK1;                            /**< Interrupt Masks 1 register, offset: 0x28 */



958       uint8_t RESERVED_2[4];



959  __IO uint32_t IFLAG1;                            /**< Interrupt Flags 1 register, offset: 0x30 */



960  __IO uint32_t CTRL2;                             /**< Control 2 register, offset: 0x34 */



961  __I  uint32_t ESR2;                              /**< Error and Status 2 register, offset: 0x38 */



962       uint8_t RESERVED_3[8];



963  __I  uint32_t CRCR;                              /**< CRC Register, offset: 0x44 */



964  __IO uint32_t RXFGMASK;                          /**< Rx FIFO Global Mask register, offset: 0x48 */



965  __I  uint32_t RXFIR;                             /**< Rx FIFO Information Register, offset: 0x4C */



966  __IO uint32_t CBT;                               /**< CAN Bit Timing Register, offset: 0x50 */



967       uint8_t RESERVED_4[44];



968  __IO uint32_t RAMn[CAN_RAMn_COUNT];              /**< Embedded RAM, array offset: 0x80, array step: 0x4 */



969       uint8_t RESERVED_5[1536];



970  __IO uint32_t RXIMR[CAN_RXIMR_COUNT];            /**< Rx Individual Mask Registers, array offset: 0x880, array step: 0x4 */



971       uint8_t RESERVED_6[512];



972  __IO uint32_t CTRL1_PN;                          /**< Pretended Networking Control 1 Register, offset: 0xB00 */



973  __IO uint32_t CTRL2_PN;                          /**< Pretended Networking Control 2 Register, offset: 0xB04 */



974  __IO uint32_t WU_MTC;                            /**< Pretended Networking Wake Up Match Register, offset: 0xB08 */



975  __IO uint32_t FLT_ID1;                           /**< Pretended Networking ID Filter 1 Register, offset: 0xB0C */



976  __IO uint32_t FLT_DLC;                           /**< Pretended Networking DLC Filter Register, offset: 0xB10 */



977  __IO uint32_t PL1_LO;                            /**< Pretended Networking Payload Low Filter 1 Register, offset: 0xB14 */



978  __IO uint32_t PL1_HI;                            /**< Pretended Networking Payload High Filter 1 Register, offset: 0xB18 */



979  __IO uint32_t FLT_ID2_IDMASK;                    /**< Pretended Networking ID Filter 2 Register / ID Mask Register, offset: 0xB1C */



980  __IO uint32_t PL2_PLMASK_LO;                     /**< Pretended Networking Payload Low Filter 2 Register / Payload Low Mask Register, offset: 0xB20 */



981  __IO uint32_t PL2_PLMASK_HI;                     /**< Pretended Networking Payload High Filter 2 low order bits / Payload High Mask Register, offset: 0xB24 */



982       uint8_t RESERVED_7[24];



983  struct {                                         /* offset: 0xB40, array step: 0x10 */



984    __I  uint32_t WMBn_CS;                           /**< Wake Up Message Buffer Register for C/S, array offset: 0xB40, array step: 0x10 */



985    __I  uint32_t WMBn_ID;                           /**< Wake Up Message Buffer Register for ID, array offset: 0xB44, array step: 0x10 */



986    __I  uint32_t WMBn_D03;                          /**< Wake Up Message Buffer Register for Data 0-3, array offset: 0xB48, array step: 0x10 */



987    __I  uint32_t WMBn_D47;                          /**< Wake Up Message Buffer Register Data 4-7, array offset: 0xB4C, array step: 0x10 */



988  } WMB[CAN_WMB_COUNT];



989       uint8_t RESERVED_8[128];



990  __IO uint32_t FDCTRL;                            /**< CAN FD Control Register, offset: 0xC00 */



991  __IO uint32_t FDCBT;                             /**< CAN FD Bit Timing Register, offset: 0xC04 */



992  __I  uint32_t FDCRC;                             /**< CAN FD CRC Register, offset: 0xC08 */



993} CAN_Type, *CAN_MemMapPtr;



994



995 /** Number of instances of the CAN module. */



996#define CAN_INSTANCE_COUNT                       (3u)

999/* CAN - Peripheral instance base addresses */



1000/** Peripheral CAN0 base address */



1001#define CAN0_BASE                                (0x40024000u)



1002/** Peripheral CAN0 base pointer */



1003#define CAN0                                     ((CAN_Type *)CAN0_BASE)



1004/** Peripheral CAN1 base address */



1005#define CAN1_BASE                                (0x40025000u)



1006/** Peripheral CAN1 base pointer */



1007#define CAN1                                     ((CAN_Type *)CAN1_BASE)



1008/** Peripheral CAN2 base address */



1009#define CAN2_BASE                                (0x4002B000u)



1010/** Peripheral CAN2 base pointer */



1011#define CAN2                                     ((CAN_Type *)CAN2_BASE)



1012/** Array initializer of CAN peripheral base addresses */



1013#define CAN_BASE_ADDRS                           { CAN0_BASE, CAN1_BASE, CAN2_BASE }



1014/** Array initializer of CAN peripheral base pointers */



1015#define CAN_BASE_PTRS                            { CAN0, CAN1, CAN2 }



1016 /** Number of interrupt vector arrays for the CAN module. */



1017#define CAN_IRQS_ARR_COUNT                       (7u)



1018 /** Number of interrupt channels for the Rx_Warning type of CAN module. */



1019#define CAN_Rx_Warning_IRQS_CH_COUNT             (1u)



1020 /** Number of interrupt channels for the Tx_Warning type of CAN module. */



1021#define CAN_Tx_Warning_IRQS_CH_COUNT             (1u)



1022 /** Number of interrupt channels for the Wake_Up type of CAN module. */



1023#define CAN_Wake_Up_IRQS_CH_COUNT                (1u)



1024 /** Number of interrupt channels for the Error type of CAN module. */



1025#define CAN_Error_IRQS_CH_COUNT                  (1u)



1026 /** Number of interrupt channels for the Bus_Off type of CAN module. */



1027#define CAN_Bus_Off_IRQS_CH_COUNT                (1u)



1028 /** Number of interrupt channels for the ORed_0_15_MB type of CAN module. */



1029#define CAN_ORed_0_15_MB_IRQS_CH_COUNT           (1u)



1030 /** Number of interrupt channels for the ORed_16_31_MB type of CAN module. */



1031#define CAN_ORed_16_31_MB_IRQS_CH_COUNT          (1u)



1032/** Interrupt vectors for the CAN peripheral type */



1033#define CAN_Rx_Warning_IRQS                      { CAN0_ORed_IRQn, CAN1_ORed_IRQn, CAN2_ORed_IRQn }



1034#define CAN_Tx_Warning_IRQS                      { CAN0_ORed_IRQn, CAN1_ORed_IRQn, CAN2_ORed_IRQn }



1035#define CAN_Wake_Up_IRQS                         { CAN0_Wake_Up_IRQn, NotAvail_IRQn, NotAvail_IRQn }



1036#define CAN_Error_IRQS                           { CAN0_Error_IRQn, CAN1_Error_IRQn, CAN2_Error_IRQn }



1037#define CAN_Bus_Off_IRQS                         { CAN0_ORed_IRQn, CAN1_ORed_IRQn, CAN2_ORed_IRQn }



1038#define CAN_ORed_0_15_MB_IRQS                    { CAN0_ORed_0_15_MB_IRQn, CAN1_ORed_0_15_MB_IRQn, CAN2_ORed_0_15_MB_IRQn }



1039#define CAN_ORed_16_31_MB_IRQS                   { CAN0_ORed_16_31_MB_IRQn, NotAvail_IRQn, NotAvail_IRQn }

2266  __O  uint8_t SERQ;                               /**< Set Enable Request Register, offset: 0x1B */



2267  __O  uint8_t CDNE;                               /**< Clear DONE Status Bit Register, offset: 0x1C */



2268  __O  uint8_t SSRT;                               /**< Set START Bit Register, offset: 0x1D */



2269  __O  uint8_t CERR;                               /**< Clear Error Register, offset: 0x1E */



2270  __O  uint8_t CINT;                               /**< Clear Interrupt Request Register, offset: 0x1F */



2271       uint8_t RESERVED_2[4];

2280  __IO uint8_t DCHPRI[DMA_DCHPRI_COUNT];           /**< Channel n Priority Register, array offset: 0x100, array step: 0x1 */



2281       uint8_t RESERVED_7[3824];



2282  struct {                                         /* offset: 0x1000, array step: 0x20 */



2283    __IO uint32_t SADDR;                             /**< TCD Source Address, array offset: 0x1000, array step: 0x20 */



2284    __IO uint16_t SOFF;                              /**< TCD Signed Source Address Offset, array offset: 0x1004, array step: 0x20 */



2285    __IO uint16_t ATTR;                              /**< TCD Transfer Attributes, array offset: 0x1006, array step: 0x20 */

2289      __IO uint32_t MLOFFYES;                          /**< TCD Signed Minor Loop Offset (Minor Loop Mapping and Offset Enabled), array offset: 0x1008, array step: 0x20 */



2290    } NBYTES;



2291    __IO uint32_t SLAST;                             /**< TCD Last Source Address Adjustment, array offset: 0x100C, array step: 0x20 */



2292    __IO uint32_t DADDR;                             /**< TCD Destination Address, array offset: 0x1010, array step: 0x20 */



2293    __IO uint16_t DOFF;                              /**< TCD Signed Destination Address Offset, array offset: 0x1014, array step: 0x20 */

2296      __IO uint16_t ELINKYES;                          /**< TCD Current Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Enabled), array offset: 0x1016, array step: 0x20 */



2297    } CITER;



2298    __IO uint32_t DLASTSGA;                          /**< TCD Last Destination Address Adjustment/Scatter Gather Address, array offset: 0x1018, array step: 0x20 */

2300    union {                                          /* offset: 0x101E, array step: 0x20 */



2301      __IO uint16_t ELINKNO;                           /**< TCD Beginning Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Disabled), array offset: 0x101E, array step: 0x20 */



2302      __IO uint16_t ELINKYES;                          /**< TCD Beginning Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Enabled), array offset: 0x101E, array step: 0x20 */



2303    } BITER;

3778/** FTFC - Size of Registers Arrays */



3779#define FTFC_FCCOB_COUNT                         12u



3780#define FTFC_FPROT_COUNT                         4u



3781



3782/** FTFC - Register Layout Typedef */



3783typedef struct {



3784  __IO uint8_t FSTAT;                              /**< Flash Status Register, offset: 0x0 */



3785  __IO uint8_t FCNFG;                              /**< Flash Configuration Register, offset: 0x1 */



3786  __I  uint8_t FSEC;                               /**< Flash Security Register, offset: 0x2 */



3787  __I  uint8_t FOPT;                               /**< Flash Option Register, offset: 0x3 */



3788  __IO uint8_t FCCOB[FTFC_FCCOB_COUNT];            /**< Flash Common Command Object Registers, array offset: 0x4, array step: 0x1 */



3789  __IO uint8_t FPROT[FTFC_FPROT_COUNT];            /**< Program Flash Protection Registers, array offset: 0x10, array step: 0x1 */



3790       uint8_t RESERVED_0[2];



3791  __IO uint8_t FEPROT;                             /**< EEPROM Protection Register, offset: 0x16 */



3792  __IO uint8_t FDPROT;                             /**< Data Flash Protection Register, offset: 0x17 */



3793       uint8_t RESERVED_1[20];



3794  __I  uint8_t FCSESTAT;                           /**< Flash CSEc Status Register, offset: 0x2C */



3795       uint8_t RESERVED_2[1];



3796  __IO uint8_t FERSTAT;                            /**< Flash Error Status Register, offset: 0x2E */



3797  __IO uint8_t FERCNFG;                            /**< Flash Error Configuration Register, offset: 0x2F */



3798} FTFC_Type, *FTFC_MemMapPtr;



3799



3800 /** Number of instances of the FTFC module. */



3801#define FTFC_INSTANCE_COUNT                      (1u)



3802



3803



3804/* FTFC - Peripheral instance base addresses */



3805/** Peripheral FTFC base address */



3806#define FTFC_BASE                                (0x40020000u)



3807/** Peripheral FTFC base pointer */



3808#define FTFC                                     ((FTFC_Type *)FTFC_BASE)



3809/** Array initializer of FTFC peripheral base addresses */



3810#define FTFC_BASE_ADDRS                          { FTFC_BASE }



3811/** Array initializer of FTFC peripheral base pointers */



3812#define FTFC_BASE_PTRS                           { FTFC }



3813 /** Number of interrupt vector arrays for the FTFC module. */



3814#define FTFC_IRQS_ARR_COUNT                      (2u)



3815 /** Number of interrupt channels for the COMMAND_COMPLETE type of FTFC module. */



3816#define FTFC_COMMAND_COMPLETE_IRQS_CH_COUNT      (1u)



3817 /** Number of interrupt channels for the READ_COLLISION type of FTFC module. */



3818#define FTFC_READ_COLLISION_IRQS_CH_COUNT        (1u)



3819/** Interrupt vectors for the FTFC peripheral type */



3820#define FTFC_COMMAND_COMPLETE_IRQS               { FTFC_IRQn }



3821#define FTFC_READ_COLLISION_IRQS                 { Read_Collision_IRQn }

3988/** FTM - Size of Registers Arrays */



3989#define FTM_CONTROLS_COUNT                       8u



3990



3991/** FTM - Register Layout Typedef */



3992typedef struct {



3993  __IO uint32_t SC;                                /**< Status And Control, offset: 0x0 */



3994  __IO uint32_t CNT;                               /**< Counter, offset: 0x4 */



3995  __IO uint32_t MOD;                               /**< Modulo, offset: 0x8 */



3996  struct {                                         /* offset: 0xC, array step: 0x8 */



3997    __IO uint32_t CnSC;                              /**< Channel (n) Status And Control, array offset: 0xC, array step: 0x8 */



3998    __IO uint32_t CnV;                               /**< Channel (n) Value, array offset: 0x10, array step: 0x8 */



3999  } CONTROLS[FTM_CONTROLS_COUNT];



4000  __IO uint32_t CNTIN;                             /**< Counter Initial Value, offset: 0x4C */



4001  __IO uint32_t STATUS;                            /**< Capture And Compare Status, offset: 0x50 */



4002  __IO uint32_t MODE;                              /**< Features Mode Selection, offset: 0x54 */



4003  __IO uint32_t SYNC;                              /**< Synchronization, offset: 0x58 */



4004  __IO uint32_t OUTINIT;                           /**< Initial State For Channels Output, offset: 0x5C */



4005  __IO uint32_t OUTMASK;                           /**< Output Mask, offset: 0x60 */



4006  __IO uint32_t COMBINE;                           /**< Function For Linked Channels, offset: 0x64 */



4007  __IO uint32_t DEADTIME;                          /**< Deadtime Configuration, offset: 0x68 */



4008  __IO uint32_t EXTTRIG;                           /**< FTM External Trigger, offset: 0x6C */



4009  __IO uint32_t POL;                               /**< Channels Polarity, offset: 0x70 */



4010  __IO uint32_t FMS;                               /**< Fault Mode Status, offset: 0x74 */



4011  __IO uint32_t FILTER;                            /**< Input Capture Filter Control, offset: 0x78 */



4012  __IO uint32_t FLTCTRL;                           /**< Fault Control, offset: 0x7C */



4013  __IO uint32_t QDCTRL;                            /**< Quadrature Decoder Control And Status, offset: 0x80 */



4014  __IO uint32_t CONF;                              /**< Configuration, offset: 0x84 */



4015  __IO uint32_t FLTPOL;                            /**< FTM Fault Input Polarity, offset: 0x88 */



4016  __IO uint32_t SYNCONF;                           /**< Synchronization Configuration, offset: 0x8C */



4017  __IO uint32_t INVCTRL;                           /**< FTM Inverting Control, offset: 0x90 */



4018  __IO uint32_t SWOCTRL;                           /**< FTM Software Output Control, offset: 0x94 */



4019  __IO uint32_t PWMLOAD;                           /**< FTM PWM Load, offset: 0x98 */



4020  __IO uint32_t HCR;                               /**< Half Cycle Register, offset: 0x9C */



4021  __IO uint32_t PAIR0DEADTIME;                     /**< Pair 0 Deadtime Configuration, offset: 0xA0 */



4022       uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];



4023  __IO uint32_t PAIR1DEADTIME;                     /**< Pair 1 Deadtime Configuration, offset: 0xA8 */



4024       uint8_t RESERVED_1[4];



4025  __IO uint32_t PAIR2DEADTIME;                     /**< Pair 2 Deadtime Configuration, offset: 0xB0 */



4026       uint8_t RESERVED_2[4];



4027  __IO uint32_t PAIR3DEADTIME;                     /**< Pair 3 Deadtime Configuration, offset: 0xB8 */



4028} FTM_Type, *FTM_MemMapPtr;



4029

5017



5018/** GPIO - Size of Registers Arrays */



5019



5020/** GPIO - Register Layout Typedef */



5021typedef struct {



5022  __IO uint32_t PDOR;                              /**< Port Data Output Register, offset: 0x0 */



5023  __O  uint32_t PSOR;                              /**< Port Set Output Register, offset: 0x4 */



5024  __O  uint32_t PCOR;                              /**< Port Clear Output Register, offset: 0x8 */



5025  __O  uint32_t PTOR;                              /**< Port Toggle Output Register, offset: 0xC */



5026  __I  uint32_t PDIR;                              /**< Port Data Input Register, offset: 0x10 */



5027  __IO uint32_t PDDR;                              /**< Port Data Direction Register, offset: 0x14 */



5028  __IO uint32_t PIDR;                              /**< Port Input Disable Register, offset: 0x18 */



5029} GPIO_Type, *GPIO_MemMapPtr;



5030



5031 /** Number of instances of the GPIO module. */



5032#define GPIO_INSTANCE_COUNT                      (5u)



5033



5034



5035/* GPIO - Peripheral instance base addresses */



5036/** Peripheral PTA base address */



5037#define PTA_BASE                                 (0x400FF000u)



5038/** Peripheral PTA base pointer */



5039#define PTA                                      ((GPIO_Type *)PTA_BASE)



5040/** Peripheral PTB base address */



5041#define PTB_BASE                                 (0x400FF040u)



5042/** Peripheral PTB base pointer */



5043#define PTB                                      ((GPIO_Type *)PTB_BASE)



5044/** Peripheral PTC base address */



5045#define PTC_BASE                                 (0x400FF080u)



5046/** Peripheral PTC base pointer */



5047#define PTC                                      ((GPIO_Type *)PTC_BASE)



5048/** Peripheral PTD base address */



5049#define PTD_BASE                                 (0x400FF0C0u)



5050/** Peripheral PTD base pointer */



5051#define PTD                                      ((GPIO_Type *)PTD_BASE)



5052/** Peripheral PTE base address */



5053#define PTE_BASE                                 (0x400FF100u)



5054/** Peripheral PTE base pointer */



5055#define PTE                                      ((GPIO_Type *)PTE_BASE)



5056/** Array initializer of GPIO peripheral base addresses */



5057#define GPIO_BASE_ADDRS                          { PTA_BASE, PTB_BASE, PTC_BASE, PTD_BASE, PTE_BASE }



5058/** Array initializer of GPIO peripheral base pointers */



5059#define GPIO_BASE_PTRS                           { PTA, PTB, PTC, PTD, PTE }

5337/** LPI2C - Register Layout Typedef */



5338typedef struct {



5339  __I  uint32_t VERID;                             /**< Version ID Register, offset: 0x0 */



5340  __I  uint32_t PARAM;                             /**< Parameter Register, offset: 0x4 */



5341       uint8_t RESERVED_0[8];



5342  __IO uint32_t MCR;                               /**< Master Control Register, offset: 0x10 */



5343  __IO uint32_t MSR;                               /**< Master Status Register, offset: 0x14 */



5344  __IO uint32_t MIER;                              /**< Master Interrupt Enable Register, offset: 0x18 */



5345  __IO uint32_t MDER;                              /**< Master DMA Enable Register, offset: 0x1C */



5346  __IO uint32_t MCFGR0;                            /**< Master Configuration Register 0, offset: 0x20 */



5347  __IO uint32_t MCFGR1;                            /**< Master Configuration Register 1, offset: 0x24 */



5348  __IO uint32_t MCFGR2;                            /**< Master Configuration Register 2, offset: 0x28 */



5349  __IO uint32_t MCFGR3;                            /**< Master Configuration Register 3, offset: 0x2C */



5350       uint8_t RESERVED_1[16];



5351  __IO uint32_t MDMR;                              /**< Master Data Match Register, offset: 0x40 */



5352       uint8_t RESERVED_2[4];



5353  __IO uint32_t MCCR0;                             /**< Master Clock Configuration Register 0, offset: 0x48 */



5354       uint8_t RESERVED_3[4];



5355  __IO uint32_t MCCR1;                             /**< Master Clock Configuration Register 1, offset: 0x50 */



5356       uint8_t RESERVED_4[4];



5357  __IO uint32_t MFCR;                              /**< Master FIFO Control Register, offset: 0x58 */



5358  __I  uint32_t MFSR;                              /**< Master FIFO Status Register, offset: 0x5C */



5359  __IO uint32_t MTDR;                              /**< Master Transmit Data Register, offset: 0x60 */



5360       uint8_t RESERVED_5[12];



5361  __I  uint32_t MRDR;                              /**< Master Receive Data Register, offset: 0x70 */



5362       uint8_t RESERVED_6[156];



5363  __IO uint32_t SCR;                               /**< Slave Control Register, offset: 0x110 */



5364  __IO uint32_t SSR;                               /**< Slave Status Register, offset: 0x114 */



5365  __IO uint32_t SIER;                              /**< Slave Interrupt Enable Register, offset: 0x118 */



5366  __IO uint32_t SDER;                              /**< Slave DMA Enable Register, offset: 0x11C */



5367       uint8_t RESERVED_7[4];



5368  __IO uint32_t SCFGR1;                            /**< Slave Configuration Register 1, offset: 0x124 */



5369  __IO uint32_t SCFGR2;                            /**< Slave Configuration Register 2, offset: 0x128 */



5370       uint8_t RESERVED_8[20];



5371  __IO uint32_t SAMR;                              /**< Slave Address Match Register, offset: 0x140 */



5372       uint8_t RESERVED_9[12];



5373  __I  uint32_t SASR;                              /**< Slave Address Status Register, offset: 0x150 */



5374  __IO uint32_t STAR;                              /**< Slave Transmit ACK Register, offset: 0x154 */



5375       uint8_t RESERVED_10[8];



5376  __IO uint32_t STDR;                              /**< Slave Transmit Data Register, offset: 0x160 */



5377       uint8_t RESERVED_11[12];



5378  __I  uint32_t SRDR;                              /**< Slave Receive Data Register, offset: 0x170 */



5379} LPI2C_Type, *LPI2C_MemMapPtr;

5962/** LPIT - Size of Registers Arrays */



5963#define LPIT_TMR_COUNT                           4u



5964



5965/** LPIT - Register Layout Typedef */



5966typedef struct {



5967  __I  uint32_t VERID;                             /**< Version ID Register, offset: 0x0 */



5968  __I  uint32_t PARAM;                             /**< Parameter Register, offset: 0x4 */



5969  __IO uint32_t MCR;                               /**< Module Control Register, offset: 0x8 */



5970  __IO uint32_t MSR;                               /**< Module Status Register, offset: 0xC */



5971  __IO uint32_t MIER;                              /**< Module Interrupt Enable Register, offset: 0x10 */



5972  __IO uint32_t SETTEN;                            /**< Set Timer Enable Register, offset: 0x14 */



5973  __IO uint32_t CLRTEN;                            /**< Clear Timer Enable Register, offset: 0x18 */



5974       uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];



5975  struct {                                         /* offset: 0x20, array step: 0x10 */



5976    __IO uint32_t TVAL;                              /**< Timer Value Register, array offset: 0x20, array step: 0x10 */



5977    __I  uint32_t CVAL;                              /**< Current Timer Value, array offset: 0x24, array step: 0x10 */



5978    __IO uint32_t TCTRL;                             /**< Timer Control Register, array offset: 0x28, array step: 0x10 */



5979         uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];



5980  } TMR[LPIT_TMR_COUNT];



5981} LPIT_Type, *LPIT_MemMapPtr;

5984#define LPIT_INSTANCE_COUNT                      (1u)

6202  __IO uint32_t FCR;                               /**< FIFO Control Register, offset: 0x58 */



6203  __I  uint32_t FSR;                               /**< FIFO Status Register, offset: 0x5C */



6204  __IO uint32_t TCR;                               /**< Transmit Command Register, offset: 0x60 */



6205  __O  uint32_t TDR;                               /**< Transmit Data Register, offset: 0x64 */



6206       uint8_t RESERVED_4[8];



6207  __I  uint32_t RSR;                               /**< Receive Status Register, offset: 0x70 */



6208  __I  uint32_t RDR;                               /**< Receive Data Register, offset: 0x74 */

6566/** LPTMR - Size of Registers Arrays */



6567



6568/** LPTMR - Register Layout Typedef */



6569typedef struct {



6570  __IO uint32_t CSR;                               /**< Low Power Timer Control Status Register, offset: 0x0 */



6571  __IO uint32_t PSR;                               /**< Low Power Timer Prescale Register, offset: 0x4 */

6684/** LPUART - Register Layout Typedef */



6685typedef struct {



6686  __I  uint32_t VERID;                             /**< Version ID Register, offset: 0x0 */



6687  __I  uint32_t PARAM;                             /**< Parameter Register, offset: 0x4 */



6688  __IO uint32_t GLOBAL;                            /**< LPUART Global Register, offset: 0x8 */



6689  __IO uint32_t PINCFG;                            /**< LPUART Pin Configuration Register, offset: 0xC */



6690  __IO uint32_t BAUD;                              /**< LPUART Baud Rate Register, offset: 0x10 */



6691  __IO uint32_t STAT;                              /**< LPUART Status Register, offset: 0x14 */



6692  __IO uint32_t CTRL;                              /**< LPUART Control Register, offset: 0x18 */



6693  __IO uint32_t DATA;                              /**< LPUART Data Register, offset: 0x1C */



6694  __IO uint32_t MATCH;                             /**< LPUART Match Address Register, offset: 0x20 */



6695  __IO uint32_t MODIR;                             /**< LPUART Modem IrDA Register, offset: 0x24 */



6696  __IO uint32_t FIFO;                              /**< LPUART FIFO Register, offset: 0x28 */



6697  __IO uint32_t WATER;                             /**< LPUART Watermark Register, offset: 0x2C */



6698} LPUART_Type, *LPUART_MemMapPtr;

7210/** MCM - Size of Registers Arrays */



7211#define MCM_LMDR_COUNT                           2u



7212



7213/** MCM - Register Layout Typedef */



7214typedef struct {



7215       uint8_t RESERVED_0[8];



7216  __I  uint16_t PLASC;                             /**< Crossbar Switch (AXBS) Slave Configuration, offset: 0x8 */



7217  __I  uint16_t PLAMC;                             /**< Crossbar Switch (AXBS) Master Configuration, offset: 0xA */



7218  __IO uint32_t CPCR;                              /**< Core Platform Control Register, offset: 0xC */



7219  __IO uint32_t ISCR;                              /**< Interrupt Status and Control Register, offset: 0x10 */



7220       uint8_t RESERVED_1[28];



7221  __IO uint32_t PID;                               /**< Process ID Register, offset: 0x30 */



7222       uint8_t RESERVED_2[12];



7223  __IO uint32_t CPO;                               /**< Compute Operation Control Register, offset: 0x40 */



7224       uint8_t RESERVED_3[956];



7225  __IO uint32_t LMDR[MCM_LMDR_COUNT];              /**< Local Memory Descriptor Register, array offset: 0x400, array step: 0x4 */



7226  __IO uint32_t LMDR2;                             /**< Local Memory Descriptor Register2, offset: 0x408 */



7227       uint8_t RESERVED_4[116];



7228  __IO uint32_t LMPECR;                            /**< LMEM Parity and ECC Control Register, offset: 0x480 */



7229       uint8_t RESERVED_5[4];



7230  __IO uint32_t LMPEIR;                            /**< LMEM Parity and ECC Interrupt Register, offset: 0x488 */



7231       uint8_t RESERVED_6[4];



7232  __I  uint32_t LMFAR;                             /**< LMEM Fault Address Register, offset: 0x490 */



7233  __I  uint32_t LMFATR;                            /**< LMEM Fault Attribute Register, offset: 0x494 */



7234       uint8_t RESERVED_7[8];



7235  __I  uint32_t LMFDHR;                            /**< LMEM Fault Data High Register, offset: 0x4A0 */



7236  __I  uint32_t LMFDLR;                            /**< LMEM Fault Data Low Register, offset: 0x4A4 */



7237} MCM_Type, *MCM_MemMapPtr;



7238

7543/** MPU - Size of Registers Arrays */



7544#define MPU_EAR_EDR_COUNT                        4u



7545#define MPU_RGD_COUNT                            8u



7546#define MPU_RGDAAC_COUNT                         8u



7547



7548/** MPU - Register Layout Typedef */



7549typedef struct {



7550  __IO uint32_t CESR;                              /**< Control/Error Status Register, offset: 0x0 */



7551       uint8_t RESERVED_0[12];



7552  struct {                                         /* offset: 0x10, array step: 0x8 */



7553    __I  uint32_t EAR;                               /**< Error Address Register, slave port



7554    							0..Error Address Register, slave port



7555    							3, array offset: 0x10, array step: 0x8 */



7556    __I  uint32_t EDR;                               /**< Error Detail Register, slave port



7557    							0..Error Detail Register, slave port



7558    							3, array offset: 0x14, array step: 0x8 */



7559  } EAR_EDR[MPU_EAR_EDR_COUNT];



7560       uint8_t RESERVED_1[976];



7561  struct {                                         /* offset: 0x400, array step: 0x10 */



7562    __IO uint32_t WORD0;                             /**< Region Descriptor 0, Word 0..Region Descriptor 7, Word 0, array offset: 0x400, array step: 0x10 */



7563    __IO uint32_t WORD1;                             /**< Region Descriptor 0, Word 1..Region Descriptor 7, Word 1, array offset: 0x404, array step: 0x10 */



7564    __IO uint32_t WORD2;                             /**< Region Descriptor 0, Word 2..Region Descriptor 7, Word 2, array offset: 0x408, array step: 0x10 */



7565    __IO uint32_t WORD3;                             /**< Region Descriptor 0, Word 3..Region Descriptor 7, Word 3, array offset: 0x40C, array step: 0x10 */



7566  } RGD[MPU_RGD_COUNT];



7567       uint8_t RESERVED_2[896];



7568  __IO uint32_t RGDAAC[MPU_RGDAAC_COUNT];          /**< Region Descriptor Alternate Access Control



7569  							0..Region Descriptor Alternate Access Control



7570  							7, array offset: 0x800, array step: 0x4 */



7571} MPU_Type, *MPU_MemMapPtr;



7572



7573 /** Number of instances of the MPU module. */



7574#define MPU_INSTANCE_COUNT                       (1u)



7575

7580/** Peripheral MPU base pointer */



7581#define MPU                                      ((MPU_Type *)MPU_BASE)

7583#define MPU_BASE_ADDRS                           { MPU_BASE }



7584/** Array initializer of MPU peripheral base pointers */



7585#define MPU_BASE_PTRS                            { MPU }

7845/** MSCM - Size of Registers Arrays */



7846#define MSCM_OCMDR_COUNT                         3u



7847



7848/** MSCM - Register Layout Typedef */



7849typedef struct {



7850  __I  uint32_t CPxTYPE;                           /**< Processor X Type Register, offset: 0x0 */



7851  __I  uint32_t CPxNUM;                            /**< Processor X Number Register, offset: 0x4 */



7852  __I  uint32_t CPxMASTER;                         /**< Processor X Master Register, offset: 0x8 */



7853  __I  uint32_t CPxCOUNT;                          /**< Processor X Count Register, offset: 0xC */



7854  __I  uint32_t CPxCFG0;                           /**< Processor X Configuration Register 0, offset: 0x10 */



7855  __I  uint32_t CPxCFG1;                           /**< Processor X Configuration Register 1, offset: 0x14 */



7856  __I  uint32_t CPxCFG2;                           /**< Processor X Configuration Register 2, offset: 0x18 */



7857  __I  uint32_t CPxCFG3;                           /**< Processor X Configuration Register 3, offset: 0x1C */



7858  __I  uint32_t CP0TYPE;                           /**< Processor 0 Type Register, offset: 0x20 */



7859  __I  uint32_t CP0NUM;                            /**< Processor 0 Number Register, offset: 0x24 */



7860  __I  uint32_t CP0MASTER;                         /**< Processor 0 Master Register, offset: 0x28 */



7861  __I  uint32_t CP0COUNT;                          /**< Processor 0 Count Register, offset: 0x2C */



7862  __I  uint32_t CP0CFG0;                           /**< Processor 0 Configuration Register 0, offset: 0x30 */



7863  __I  uint32_t CP0CFG1;                           /**< Processor 0 Configuration Register 1, offset: 0x34 */



7864  __I  uint32_t CP0CFG2;                           /**< Processor 0 Configuration Register 2, offset: 0x38 */



7865  __I  uint32_t CP0CFG3;                           /**< Processor 0 Configuration Register 3, offset: 0x3C */



7866       uint8_t RESERVED_0[960];



7867  __IO uint32_t OCMDR[MSCM_OCMDR_COUNT];           /**< On-Chip Memory Descriptor Register, array offset: 0x400, array step: 0x4 */



7868} MSCM_Type, *MSCM_MemMapPtr;



7869



7870 /** Number of instances of the MSCM module. */



7871#define MSCM_INSTANCE_COUNT                      (1u)

7880#define MSCM_BASE_ADDRS                          { MSCM_BASE }



7881/** Array initializer of MSCM peripheral base pointers */



7882#define MSCM_BASE_PTRS                           { MSCM }

8243/** PDB - Register Layout Typedef */



8244typedef struct {



8245  __IO uint32_t SC;                                /**< Status and Control register, offset: 0x0 */



8246  __IO uint32_t MOD;                               /**< Modulus register, offset: 0x4 */



8247  __I  uint32_t CNT;                               /**< Counter register, offset: 0x8 */



8248  __IO uint32_t IDLY;                              /**< Interrupt Delay register, offset: 0xC */



8249  struct {                                         /* offset: 0x10, array step: 0x28 */



8250    __IO uint32_t C1;                                /**< Channel n Control register 1, array offset: 0x10, array step: 0x28 */



8251    __IO uint32_t S;                                 /**< Channel n Status register, array offset: 0x14, array step: 0x28 */



8252    __IO uint32_t DLY[PDB_DLY_COUNT];                /**< Channel n Delay 0 register..Channel n Delay 7 register, array offset: 0x18, array step: index*0x28, index2*0x4 */



8253  } CH[PDB_CH_COUNT];



8254       uint8_t RESERVED_0[304];



8255  __IO uint32_t POEN;                              /**< Pulse-Out n Enable register, offset: 0x190 */



8256  union {                                          /* offset: 0x194, array step: 0x4 */



8257    __IO uint32_t PODLY;                             /**< Pulse-Out n Delay register, array offset: 0x194, array step: 0x4 */



8258    struct {                                         /* offset: 0x194, array step: 0x4 */



8259      __IO uint16_t DLY2;                              /**< PDB1_DLY2 register...PDB0_DLY2 register., array offset: 0x194, array step: 0x4 */



8260      __IO uint16_t DLY1;                              /**< PDB1_DLY1 register...PDB0_DLY1 register., array offset: 0x196, array step: 0x4 */



8261    } ACCESS16BIT;



8262  } POnDLY[PDB_POnDLY_COUNT];



8263} PDB_Type, *PDB_MemMapPtr;

8551/** PORT - Size of Registers Arrays */



8552#define PORT_PCR_COUNT                           32u



8553



8554/** PORT - Register Layout Typedef */



8555typedef struct {



8556  __IO uint32_t PCR[PORT_PCR_COUNT];               /**< Pin Control Register n, array offset: 0x0, array step: 0x4 */



8557  __O  uint32_t GPCLR;                             /**< Global Pin Control Low Register, offset: 0x80 */



8558  __O  uint32_t GPCHR;                             /**< Global Pin Control High Register, offset: 0x84 */



8559  __O  uint32_t GICLR;                             /**< Global Interrupt Control Low Register, offset: 0x88 */



8560  __O  uint32_t GICHR;                             /**< Global Interrupt Control High Register, offset: 0x8C */



8561       uint8_t RESERVED_0[16];



8562  __IO uint32_t ISFR;                              /**< Interrupt Status Flag Register, offset: 0xA0 */



8563       uint8_t RESERVED_1[28];



8564  __IO uint32_t DFER;                              /**< Digital Filter Enable Register, offset: 0xC0 */



8565  __IO uint32_t DFCR;                              /**< Digital Filter Clock Register, offset: 0xC4 */



8566  __IO uint32_t DFWR;                              /**< Digital Filter Width Register, offset: 0xC8 */



8567} PORT_Type, *PORT_MemMapPtr;

8570#define PORT_INSTANCE_COUNT                      (5u)

9005/** RTC - Size of Registers Arrays */



9006



9007/** RTC - Register Layout Typedef */



9008typedef struct {



9009  __IO uint32_t TSR;                               /**< RTC Time Seconds Register, offset: 0x0 */



9010  __IO uint32_t TPR;                               /**< RTC Time Prescaler Register, offset: 0x4 */



9011  __IO uint32_t TAR;                               /**< RTC Time Alarm Register, offset: 0x8 */



9012  __IO uint32_t TCR;                               /**< RTC Time Compensation Register, offset: 0xC */



9013  __IO uint32_t CR;                                /**< RTC Control Register, offset: 0x10 */



9014  __IO uint32_t SR;                                /**< RTC Status Register, offset: 0x14 */



9015  __IO uint32_t LR;                                /**< RTC Lock Register, offset: 0x18 */



9016  __IO uint32_t IER;                               /**< RTC Interrupt Enable Register, offset: 0x1C */



9017} RTC_Type, *RTC_MemMapPtr;



9018



9019 /** Number of instances of the RTC module. */



9020#define RTC_INSTANCE_COUNT                       (1u)



9021



9022



9023/* RTC - Peripheral instance base addresses */



9024/** Peripheral RTC base address */



9025#define RTC_BASE                                 (0x4003D000u)



9026/** Peripheral RTC base pointer */



9027#define RTC                                      ((RTC_Type *)RTC_BASE)



9028/** Array initializer of RTC peripheral base addresses */



9029#define RTC_BASE_ADDRS                           { RTC_BASE }



9030/** Array initializer of RTC peripheral base pointers */



9031#define RTC_BASE_PTRS                            { RTC }



9032 /** Number of interrupt vector arrays for the RTC module. */



9033#define RTC_IRQS_ARR_COUNT                       (2u)



9034 /** Number of interrupt channels for the RTC module. */



9035#define RTC_IRQS_CH_COUNT                        (1u)



9036 /** Number of interrupt channels for the SECONDS type of RTC module. */



9037#define RTC_SECONDS_IRQS_CH_COUNT                (1u)



9038/** Interrupt vectors for the RTC peripheral type */



9039#define RTC_IRQS                                 { RTC_IRQn }



9040#define RTC_SECONDS_IRQS                         { RTC_Seconds_IRQn }

9190#define S32_NVIC_ICER_COUNT                      8u



9191#define S32_NVIC_ISPR_COUNT                      8u



9192#define S32_NVIC_ICPR_COUNT                      8u



9193#define S32_NVIC_IABR_COUNT                      8u



9194#define S32_NVIC_IP_COUNT                        240u



9195



9196/** S32_NVIC - Register Layout Typedef */



9197typedef struct {



9198  __IO uint32_t ISER[S32_NVIC_ISER_COUNT];         /**< Interrupt Set Enable Register n, array offset: 0x0, array step: 0x4 */



9199       uint8_t RESERVED_0[96];



9200  __IO uint32_t ICER[S32_NVIC_ICER_COUNT];         /**< Interrupt Clear Enable Register n, array offset: 0x80, array step: 0x4 */



9201       uint8_t RESERVED_1[96];



9202  __IO uint32_t ISPR[S32_NVIC_ISPR_COUNT];         /**< Interrupt Set Pending Register n, array offset: 0x100, array step: 0x4 */



9203       uint8_t RESERVED_2[96];



9204  __IO uint32_t ICPR[S32_NVIC_ICPR_COUNT];         /**< Interrupt Clear Pending Register n, array offset: 0x180, array step: 0x4 */



9205       uint8_t RESERVED_3[96];



9206  __IO uint32_t IABR[S32_NVIC_IABR_COUNT];         /**< Interrupt Active bit Register n, array offset: 0x200, array step: 0x4 */



9207       uint8_t RESERVED_4[224];



9208  __IO uint8_t IP[S32_NVIC_IP_COUNT];              /**< Interrupt Priority Register n, array offset: 0x300, array step: 0x1 */



9209       uint8_t RESERVED_5[2576];



9210  __O  uint32_t STIR;                              /**< Software Trigger Interrupt Register, offset: 0xE00 */



9211} S32_NVIC_Type, *S32_NVIC_MemMapPtr;



9212

9214#define S32_NVIC_INSTANCE_COUNT                  (1u)

10254/** S32_SCB - Size of Registers Arrays */



10255



10256/** S32_SCB - Register Layout Typedef */



10257typedef struct {



10258       uint8_t RESERVED_0[8];



10259  __IO uint32_t ACTLR;                             /**< Auxiliary Control Register,, offset: 0x8 */



10260       uint8_t RESERVED_1[3316];



10261  __I  uint32_t CPUID;                             /**< CPUID Base Register, offset: 0xD00 */



10262  __IO uint32_t ICSR;                              /**< Interrupt Control and State Register, offset: 0xD04 */



10263  __IO uint32_t VTOR;                              /**< Vector Table Offset Register, offset: 0xD08 */



10264  __IO uint32_t AIRCR;                             /**< Application Interrupt and Reset Control Register, offset: 0xD0C */



10265  __IO uint32_t SCR;                               /**< System Control Register, offset: 0xD10 */



10266  __IO uint32_t CCR;                               /**< Configuration and Control Register, offset: 0xD14 */



10267  __IO uint32_t SHPR1;                             /**< System Handler Priority Register 1, offset: 0xD18 */



10268  __IO uint32_t SHPR2;                             /**< System Handler Priority Register 2, offset: 0xD1C */



10269  __IO uint32_t SHPR3;                             /**< System Handler Priority Register 3, offset: 0xD20 */



10270  __IO uint32_t SHCSR;                             /**< System Handler Control and State Register, offset: 0xD24 */



10271  __IO uint32_t CFSR;                              /**< Configurable Fault Status Registers, offset: 0xD28 */



10272  __IO uint32_t HFSR;                              /**< HardFault Status register, offset: 0xD2C */



10273  __IO uint32_t DFSR;                              /**< Debug Fault Status Register, offset: 0xD30 */



10274  __IO uint32_t MMFAR;                             /**< MemManage Address Register, offset: 0xD34 */



10275  __IO uint32_t BFAR;                              /**< BusFault Address Register, offset: 0xD38 */



10276  __IO uint32_t AFSR;                              /**< Auxiliary Fault Status Register, offset: 0xD3C */



10277       uint8_t RESERVED_2[72];



10278  __IO uint32_t CPACR;                             /**< Coprocessor Access Control Register, offset: 0xD88 */



10279       uint8_t RESERVED_3[424];



10280  __IO uint32_t FPCCR;                             /**< Floating-point Context Control Register, offset: 0xF34 */



10281  __IO uint32_t FPCAR;                             /**< Floating-point Context Address Register, offset: 0xF38 */



10282  __IO uint32_t FPDSCR;                            /**< Floating-point Default Status Control Register, offset: 0xF3C */



10283} S32_SCB_Type, *S32_SCB_MemMapPtr;



10284

11201/** SIM - Size of Registers Arrays */

11203/** SIM - Register Layout Typedef */



11204typedef struct {



11205       uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];



11206  __IO uint32_t CHIPCTL;                           /**< Chip Control register, offset: 0x4 */



11207       uint8_t RESERVED_1[4];



11208  __IO uint32_t FTMOPT0;                           /**< FTM Option Register 0, offset: 0xC */



11209  __IO uint32_t LPOCLKS;                           /**< LPO Clock Select Register, offset: 0x10 */



11210       uint8_t RESERVED_2[4];



11211  __IO uint32_t ADCOPT;                            /**< ADC Options Register, offset: 0x18 */



11212  __IO uint32_t FTMOPT1;                           /**< FTM Option Register 1, offset: 0x1C */



11213  __IO uint32_t MISCTRL0;                          /**< Miscellaneous control register 0, offset: 0x20 */



11214  __I  uint32_t SDID;                              /**< System Device Identification Register, offset: 0x24 */



11215       uint8_t RESERVED_3[24];



11216  __IO uint32_t PLATCGC;                           /**< Platform Clock Gating Control Register, offset: 0x40 */



11217       uint8_t RESERVED_4[8];



11218  __IO uint32_t FCFG1;                             /**< Flash Configuration Register 1, offset: 0x4C */



11219       uint8_t RESERVED_5[4];



11220  __I  uint32_t UIDH;                              /**< Unique Identification Register High, offset: 0x54 */



11221  __I  uint32_t UIDMH;                             /**< Unique Identification Register Mid-High, offset: 0x58 */



11222  __I  uint32_t UIDML;                             /**< Unique Identification Register Mid Low, offset: 0x5C */



11223  __I  uint32_t UIDL;                              /**< Unique Identification Register Low, offset: 0x60 */



11224       uint8_t RESERVED_6[4];



11225  __IO uint32_t CLKDIV4;                           /**< System Clock Divider Register 4, offset: 0x68 */



11226  __IO uint32_t MISCTRL1;                          /**< Miscellaneous Control register 1, offset: 0x6C */



11227} SIM_Type, *SIM_MemMapPtr;

11552/** SMC - Size of Registers Arrays */



11553



11554/** SMC - Register Layout Typedef */



11555typedef struct {



11556  __I  uint32_t VERID;                             /**< SMC Version ID Register, offset: 0x0 */



11557  __I  uint32_t PARAM;                             /**< SMC Parameter Register, offset: 0x4 */



11558  __IO uint32_t PMPROT;                            /**< Power Mode Protection register, offset: 0x8 */



11559  __IO uint32_t PMCTRL;                            /**< Power Mode Control register, offset: 0xC */



11560  __IO uint32_t STOPCTRL;                          /**< Stop Control Register, offset: 0x10 */



11561  __I  uint32_t PMSTAT;                            /**< Power Mode Status register, offset: 0x14 */



11562} SMC_Type, *SMC_MemMapPtr;



11563



11564 /** Number of instances of the SMC module. */



11565#define SMC_INSTANCE_COUNT                       (1u)

11568/* SMC - Peripheral instance base addresses */



11569/** Peripheral SMC base address */



11570#define SMC_BASE                                 (0x4007E000u)



11571/** Peripheral SMC base pointer */



11572#define SMC                                      ((SMC_Type *)SMC_BASE)



11573/** Array initializer of SMC peripheral base addresses */



11574#define SMC_BASE_ADDRS                           { SMC_BASE }



11575/** Array initializer of SMC peripheral base pointers */



11576#define SMC_BASE_PTRS                            { SMC }
